DIAGNOSIS: Tiny pholcids (total length 1 
1.5 mm
), without thoracic groove, with short legs, globular opisthosoma, eight eyes; distinguished from other short-legged genera by the apophyses on the male cheliceral fangs (figs. 30, 384) and the procursus with dorsal apophysis and retrolateral pointed protrusion (figs. 383, 387).
